we can use existing tools to create a prototype of Comshell;

; sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xinit xf86-video-{intel,nouveau,amdgpu} compton i3-wm
; sudo pacman -S emacs qutebrowser mpv

; nano ~/.bash_profile
  startx
; nano ~/.xinitrc
  exec i3
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3
; cp prototype/i3.config ~/.config/i3/config

; mkdir ~/.emacs.d
; cp prototype/*.el ~/.emacs.d/
ELisp is terrible as a programming language,
  but it's pretty good as a command_line interface (ie as a shell, like Bash);
